.TH "_config_request" 9 "_config_request" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
_config_request \- main routine for sending config page requests
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" _config_request
.BI "(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc "  ","
.BI "Mpi2ConfigRequest_t *mpi_request "  ","
.BI "Mpi2ConfigReply_t *mpi_reply "  ","
.BI "int timeout "  ","
.BI "void *config_page "  ","
.BI "u16 config_page_sz "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ioc" 12
per adapter object
.IP "mpi_request" 12
request message frame
.IP "mpi_reply" 12
reply mf payload returned from firmware
.IP "timeout" 12
timeout in seconds
.IP "config_page" 12
contents of the config page
.IP "config_page_sz" 12
size of config page
.SH "CONTEXT"
sleep
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
A generic API for config page requests to firmware.

The ioc->config_cmds.status flag should be MPT3_CMD_NOT_USED before calling
this API.

The callback index is set inside `ioc->config_cb_idx.
.SH "RETURN"
0 for success, non-zero for failure.
